NCM-MCI CERTIFICATION EXAM VALIDATION LOG
==========================================
Validator: LLM-Based Assessment
Exam: NCM-MCI (Master Cluster Implementation) 6.10
Parts: Part 1 (80 questions) + Part 2 (80 questions)

KEY FACTS BASELINE:
- Stargate: Port 2009 (I/O metrics)
- Prism: Port 9440 (Web UI/API)
- Curator: Port 2010 (Background tasks)
- Zookeeper: Port 2181 (Distributed coordination)
- acli: AHV/VM management
- ncli: Cluster management
- OVS bonds: active-backup (default), balance-slb, LACP
- OpLog: Write buffer/coalescing layer (SSD)
- Unified Cache: Read cache (Content Cache)
- EC-X: Space-efficient but CPU-intensive (best for cold data)
- genesis: Service manager (restart services)

